{
  "stem": "3022.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My mother refused to go at first.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I went over there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then later my mother joined us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My little brother, at that time, all the time was still with my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Because I told you at the beginning in summer of 1939 he went to live with my paternal grandparents.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "When the war broke out, they, they took the train back to the town where my father was born which was the town where they originally came from, and my brother, my little brother stayed with them.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, in the winter of 1940-- it was a very severe winter when the-- when food was very difficult to get-- a decision was made that my mother, I, and another neighbor of ours shall go to the village where my grandparents, paternal grandparents, lived and we'd buy some food to bring back to town.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we set out on the train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We went to the town of Debica and from there we hired out a horse and a wagon.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was so cold that we ran most of the time behind the horse and the wagon-- a sled, actually, not a wagon.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we came to the little village of Wielopole where my grandparents lived and my little brother was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we started buying out, buying up food.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my little brother was, by that time, nine years old. 1940? 8 years old.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was quite proficient in, in, in going to the villages and buying poultry and eggs.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we bought enough food to take with us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We bought butter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We bought some geese that we had slaughtered.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyhow, the three of us, we packed the food, and we hired a sled to go back to, to the railway station.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
